data.text:
Richland Center is a town of 5,114 people and is the county seat for Richland County. It was founded in 1851 by Ira Hazeltine. He offered to donate land to the county if Richland Center was voted the county seat. In 1852 Wisconsin Legislature formally declared Richland Center as the seat of justice for Richland Center. The present courthouse was built in 1889.

Famous architect Frank Lloyd Wright was born in Richland Center in 1867. He designed over 1,000 structures over the course of 70 years.

Richland Center offers great neighborhoods, parks, lakes and community events. It is home to major businesses and has unique shopping and business opportunities. Enjoy the farmers market in the summer and Rotary Lights in the Park during the holidays, fishing, biking, camping, check out local landmarks like the A.D. German Warehouse, unique locations like Eagle Cave or take in a movie at the Starlite 14 Drive In movie theater.
